[
  "Michael Xie is the cofounder and chief technology officer of Fortinet, which provides cybersecurity services to businesses like Panasonic and Siemens.",
  "The Chinese native moved to North America in the 1990s to study engineering at the University of Manitoba in Canada.",
  "After graduating, Xie worked at several network security companies before cofounding Fortinet with brother Ken Xie in 2000.",
  "The duo took the California-based firm public in an IPO nine years later. ",
  "Fortinet had $2.2 billion in 2019 revenue and offers services like enterprise firewalls, cloud security and network security"
]